modules.description: Implements command-line interaction with the HiGHS solver, handling problem execution and output parsing. Operates on `Lp.Problem.t` and returns solution results with objective value and variable assignments. Used to run linear programming problems with customizable solver options and logging.

This module provides a high-level interface for solving linear programming problems using the HiGHS solver, supporting customizable options such as time limits, log output, and solution tolerances. It operates on `Lp.Problem.t` structures and returns results including objective values and variable assignments, enabling integration into applications with specific performance and logging needs. The child module handles command-line interaction, executing problems and parsing solver output to produce solution results. Together, they allow both programmatic control and external execution of LP problems with detailed feedback.
